scope.summary:
Goal: wire all native editor surfaces to the EXISTING handshake_core Flight Recorder / event ledger backend so that editor actions (document save, code edit, embed created, canvas node placed, cross-ref inserted, undo fired, route-to-stage) emit structured FlightEvent records via the existing POST /api/flight_recorder/runtime_chat_event endpoint. Additionally, DESIGN (document, do NOT build) the extension seams by which future surfaces — image/photo editor, spreadsheet, mechanical engines — will attach to the same event ledger without requiring changes to the existing emitter. Expected diff: (a) a new NativeEditorEventEmitter module in src/frontend/shared/event_emitter.rs (~250 lines) with emit_* helpers that call the backend; (b) call sites in all five pane modules; (c) a FutureSeamsDesign doc encoded as Rust trait stubs (src/frontend/shared/surface_extension_seam.rs) that compiles but is not exercised at runtime; (d) integration tests proving real FlightEvent records appear in the backend after editor actions.

Event schema mapping (native editor events use event_type='system' with structured payload; do not invent new event_types — the backend schema is closed):
  - document_saved: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'document_saved', document_id, content_hash, pane_id, actor_id }
  - code_edit: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'code_edit', file_path, line_delta, pane_id }
  - embed_created: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'embed_created', embed_kind, item_id, target_document_id, pane_id }
  - canvas_node_placed: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'canvas_node_placed', canvas_id, node_id, node_kind, pane_id }
  - cross_ref_inserted: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'cross_ref_inserted', ref_kind, symbol_entity_id, target_document_id, pane_id }
  - undo_fired: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'undo_fired', scope: 'local' | 'cross_pane', pane_id }
  - route_to_stage: { schema: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: 'route_to_stage', content_kind, source_pane_id }

Extension seam design (Rust trait stubs, COMPILE-ONLY, no runtime path built):
  pub trait EditorSurface: Send + Sync {
    fn surface_id(&self) -> &'static str;  // e.g. 'image_editor', 'spreadsheet', 'engine'
    fn on_selection_changed(&self, sel: &SharedSelection, bus: &InteractionBus);
    fn on_event_emitted(&self, event: &NativeEditorEvent, ledger: &NativeEditorEventEmitter);
    fn undo_local(&self) -> Option<UndoResult>;
    fn redo_local(&self) -> Option<UndoResult>;
  }
  // EditorSurfaceRegistry: HashMap<&'static str, Box<dyn EditorSurface>>
  // Extension surfaces register at startup; the bus iterates the registry on selection change and event emit.
  // This registry is stored in InteractionBus alongside UnifiedUndoScope.
  // DESIGN NOTE: future surfaces (image editor, spreadsheet, engine) implement EditorSurface and call
  //   bus.register_surface(box MyImageEditorSurface). They get selection events and undo integration
  //   for free. No existing code changes when a new surface is registered.

Files to CREATE:
  - src/frontend/shared/event_emitter.rs  — NativeEditorEvent { schema_version: 'hsk.native_editor@0.1', action: NativeEditorAction, pane_id: String, actor_id: String, workspace_id: String, payload: serde_json::Value }. NativeEditorEventEmitter { workspace_id: String, actor_id: String, client: Arc<HandshakeCoreClient> }. Methods: async fn emit(&self, event: NativeEditorEvent) -> Result<(), EmitError> — calls POST /api/flight_recorder/runtime_chat_event with body { schema_version: 'hsk.fr.runtime_chat@0.1', event_id, ts_utc, ... payload from NativeEditorEvent }. Convenience helpers: emit_document_saved, emit_code_edit, emit_embed_created, emit_canvas_node_placed, emit_cross_ref_inserted, emit_undo_fired, emit_route_to_stage.
  - src/frontend/shared/surface_extension_seam.rs  — EditorSurface trait + EditorSurfaceRegistry struct (DESIGN ONLY: compiles, no runtime path). Include #[allow(dead_code)] on all items. File must have a module-level doc comment: '// EXTENSION SEAM: this file is a design-only stub. Future surfaces implement EditorSurface and call bus.register_surface(). No existing production code calls into this module at runtime. See WP-KERNEL-012 MT-036 for the design contract.'.
  - src/frontend/tests/event_emitter_tests.rs  — integration tests.

Files to EDIT:
  - src/frontend/shared/mod.rs  — add `pub mod event_emitter;` and `pub mod surface_extension_seam;`
  - src/frontend/shared/interaction_bus.rs  — add NativeEditorEventEmitter and EditorSurfaceRegistry as fields; expose bus.emit_event(event) which delegates to emitter.emit(event).
  - src/frontend/panes/rich_text_editor.rs  — after every saveRichDocument call, call bus.emit_event(NativeEditorEvent::document_saved(doc_id, content_hash, pane_id, actor_id)).
  - src/frontend/panes/code_editor.rs  — after every code edit batch (debounced at 2s), call emit_code_edit.
  - src/frontend/panes/canvas_pane.rs  — after PUT /canvas/graph succeeds, call emit_canvas_node_placed for each new node.
  - src/frontend/panes/rich_text_editor.rs  — after inserting an atelier_embed or code_ref node, call emit_embed_created or emit_cross_ref_inserted.
  - src/frontend/shared/undo_stack.rs  — after each undo/redo dispatch, call bus.emit_event(NativeEditorEvent::undo_fired(scope, pane_id)).
  - src/frontend/panes/stage_pane.rs  — after route-to-stage command handler runs, call emit_route_to_stage.

Step-by-step implementation notes:
  1. NativeEditorEventEmitter.emit() must be non-blocking from the egui frame thread. Use tokio::spawn to fire the POST and ignore the join handle; log failures to a bounded in-memory error ring (cap 20) accessible via the FlightRecorderView widget (port of FlightRecorderView.tsx).
  2. Actor ID: read from app state (the current operator or model session ID). Default to 'native_editor_human' if no session is active.
  3. event_id: generate as a UUID v4 at emit time (use uuid ^1 crate, already likely in Cargo.toml).
  4. ts_utc: use chrono::Utc::now().to_rfc3339() (chrono likely already in Cargo.toml).
  5. POST /api/flight_recorder/runtime_chat_event body must match RuntimeChatEventV0_1 schema (api.ts line ~607): { schema_version: 'hsk.fr.runtime_chat@0.1', event_id, ts_utc, session_id, job_id, work_packet_id, wsid }. The native editor payload is embedded in a nested 'native_editor_event' field within the payload JSON.
  6. Batch code edit events: debounce at 2000ms using a tokio::time::sleep spawned task that is reset on each edit. Only fire emit_code_edit when the timer fires, not on every keypress.
  7. EditorSurfaceRegistry in interaction_bus.rs: HashMap<&'static str, Box<dyn EditorSurface>>. Expose bus.register_surface(s: Box<dyn EditorSurface>). On SharedSelection change: iterate registry and call s.on_selection_changed(). On emit_event: iterate and call s.on_event_emitted(). In production (before any future surface is registered) the registry is empty and the iteration is a no-op.
  8. FlightRecorderView integration: the existing FlightRecorderView.tsx is already the reference. The native version should have a FlightRecorderPane widget (or reuse the one from MT-036 as a sub-panel) that calls GET /api/flight_recorder with filters actor_id=native_editor_human and eventType=system, showing native editor events. AccessKit: pane author_id="flight-recorder-pane", role=Region; each event row author_id="fr-event-{event_id}", role=ListItem.
  9. Integration test: call saveRichDocument via the Rust IPC client, then call GET /api/flight_recorder?actor=native_editor_human, assert at least one 'document_saved' event appears in the response.
  10. Tests: (a) unit: NativeEditorEvent::document_saved serializes to correct JSON schema; (b) unit: emit() method builds the correct RuntimeChatEventV0_1 body; (c) integration (real PG): trigger document_saved event, query flight recorder, assert event present; (d) unit: EditorSurfaceRegistry with a mock surface receives on_selection_changed callback; (e) compile check: cargo check passes with surface_extension_seam.rs module included (proves trait stubs compile).

Dependencies / unblock conditions:
  - MT-031 (InteractionBus) merged — event emitter is stored in the bus.
  - MT-032 (loom block + content hash) merged — emit_document_saved needs content_hash.
  - MT-035 (undo stack) merged — emit_undo_fired call site is in undo_stack.rs.
  - uuid crate (^1) and chrono crate (^0.4) must be in Cargo.toml (likely already present).
  - POST /api/flight_recorder/runtime_chat_event endpoint confirmed in api.ts line ~2339.

Risk if missed: the Flight Recorder is the primary observability surface for swarm agents and the operator; without it, no agent can observe what the native editors are doing, breaking HBR-SWARM compliance. The extension seams, if not designed now, will require a breaking refactor when the first future surface (image editor) arrives — retrofitting is always more expensive than seam-first design.
